overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification and an existing codebase. The
  agent performed an initial assessment, identifying several gaps and missing
  features across high, medium, and low priority categories. Following this, the
  agent systematically implemented the high and medium priority items. Key
  implementations included adding a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness with
  safety warnings, integrating COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome detection
  logic into the reports, incorporating placeholder outbound links to external
  resources, and refining the Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) scoring with
  weighted calculations. Each change involved updating both the interactive UI
  components and the PDF report generation to ensure consistency and
  completeness.
